What is responsible for defining the routes of the games resource?
  The router. methods are defining the routes

What do you notice about the folder structure? Whats the client responsible for? Whats the server responsible for?
  client responsible for requesting or editing info, server responsible for getting the info or making the changes

What are the the responsibilities of server.js?
  server.js is responsible for the server side to have all relevant packages and files available for use

What are the responsibilities of the gamesRouter?
  to respond to the clients interactions

What process does the the client (front-end) use to communicate with the server?
  fetch from the baseURL, post, and delete

What optional second argument does the fetch method take? And what is it used for in this application? Hint: See Using Fetch on the MDN docs
  require

Which of the games API routes does the front-end application consume (i.e. make requests to)?
  the post method

What are we using the MongoDB Driver for?
  converts different data types
